  "sections": {
    "Description": "The jellyfish-like Psions act as support units, providing passive bonuses to theVek. The Blood Psion is distinguished by its pale pink coloration and bright red cranial nodes. This Psion provides a regeneration bonus to all other Vek units on the field. If thePsionic Receiveris active, it will also heal the player units.",
    "Strategy": "The Blood Psion is most dangerous if your squad relies on wearing down enemy Vek over several turns. Do note however that the Blood Psion heals other Vekafterenvironmental damage, such asFireorElectric Smoke, butbeforeVek attacks and blocked spawn damage; as an example, enemy Vek on fire at 1HP will die before they are healed by the Blood Psion, but enemy Vek blocking spawn points at 1HP will get healed first and still survive at 1HP at the end of the turn resolution."
  },
  "full_text": "Blood Psion\nDetails\nHealth\n2\nMove\n2\nSystems\nRegeneration\n(\nEnemy\n)\nEffect\nAll other Vek heal 1 at the start of their turn.\nSpecial\nFlying\n: Flying units can move over any terrain tile.\nBlood Psion\nis one of the\nVek\nfrom\nInto The Breach\n.\nDescription\n[\n]\nThe jellyfish-like Psions act as support units, providing passive bonuses to the\nVek\n. The Blood Psion is distinguished by its pale pink coloration and bright red cranial nodes. This Psion provides a regeneration bonus to all other Vek units on the field. If the\nPsionic Receiver\nis active, it will also heal the player units.\nStrategy\n[\n]\nThe Blood Psion is most dangerous if your squad relies on wearing down enemy Vek over several turns. Do note however that the Blood Psion heals other Vek\nafter\nenvironmental damage, such as\nFire\nor\nElectric Smoke\n, but\nbefore\nVek attacks and blocked spawn damage; as an example, enemy Vek on fire at 1HP will die before they are healed by the Blood Psion, but enemy Vek blocking spawn points at 1HP will get healed first and still survive at 1HP at the end of the turn resolution.\nv\n·\nd\n·\ne\nVek\nVek\nBeetle\n•\nBlobber\n•\nBurrower\n•\nCentipede\n•\nCrab\n•\nDigger\n•\nFirefly\n•\nHornet\n•\nLeaper\n•\nScarab\n•\nScorpion\n•\nSpider\n•\nVolatile Vek\nVek (Advanced Edition)\nBouncer\n•\nGastropod\n•\nMosquito\n•\nMoth\n•\nPlasmodia\n•\nStarfish\n•\nTumblebug\nAlpha Vek\nAlpha Beetle\n•\nAlpha Blobber\n•\nAlpha Burrower\n•\nAlpha Centipede\n•\nAlpha Crab\n•\nAlpha Digger\n•\nAlpha Firefly\n•\nAlpha Hornet\n•\nAlpha Leaper\n•\nAlpha Scarab\n•\nAlpha Scorpion\n•\nAlpha Spider\nAlpha Vek (Advanced Edition)\nAlpha Bouncer\n•\nAlpha Gastropod\n•\nAlpha Mosquito\n•\nAlpha Moth\n•\nAlpha Plasmodia\n•\nAlpha Starfish\n•\nAlpha Tumblebug\nVek Psions\nBlast Psion\n•\nBlood Psion\n•\nShell Psion\n•\nSoldier Psion\nVek Psions (Advanced Edition)\nArachnid Psion\n•\nRaging Psion\n•\nSmoldering Psion\nVek Minions\nBlob\n•\nAlpha Blob\n•\nSpiderling Egg\n•\nSpiderling\n•\nAlpha Spiderling\nVek Minions (Advanced Edition)\nSpore\n•\nAlpha Spore\n•\nVicious Spore\n•\nBlob Leader\nVek Leaders\nBeetle Leader\n•\nFirefly Leader\n•\nHornet Leader\n•\nLarge Goo\n(\nMedium Goo\n) (\nSmall Goo\n) •\nPsion Abomination\n•\nScorpion Leader\n•\nSpider Leader\nVek Leaders (Advanced Edition)\nBlobber Leader\n•\nBouncer Leader\n•\nCentipede Leader\n•\nCrab Leader\n•\nGastropod Leader\n•\nMosquito Leader\n•\nPlasmodia Leader\n•\nScarab Leader\n•\nStarfish Leader\n•\nTumblebug Leader"
